properties.description: The former studio home of the sculptor Dora Gordine and her husband the Hon. Richard Hare, a scholar of Russian art and literature. 1930s house over four floors including a flat roof terrace and views of Richmond Park.
properties.name: Dorich House Museum

properties.description: Architecturally distinguished and well-preserved, brick-built, Elizabethan Grade I listed manor house. Contains 17C wall-paintings, wood panelling, a charming walled garden and a fine Tudor turret. Many original features have been restored.

images.title: Attic showing exposed timber frame of the property.

properties.name: Eastbury Manor House

properties.description: King's Cross is a 67 acre development in Central London being transformed into a new city quarter with 20 regenerated heritage buildings, new homes, offices, public spaces, shops, galleries, bars, restaurants, schools and a university.

images.title: The Coal Office and Canal Side Steps

properties.name: King's Cross Heritage, Energy Centre and Garden Tours

properties.description: Hackney Empire is a grade II* listed building. The theatre was built as a music hall in 1901, designed by the architect Frank Matcham. It is now an exceptional variety theatre for the 21st century, serving the local community and beyond.

images.title: Hackney Empire view from the stage
Full audience for Mac DeMarco, 2023. Credit: Mark Senior

properties.name: Hackney Empire

properties.description:
Grade I listed Georgian church on the Thames. St Marys has outstanding interior and monuments; commemorating those associated with the church: Painter Turner, poet William Blake, botanist William Curtis and Benedict Arnold. 
St Marys is hosting an Open House Week Floral Festival with arrangements and installations by local and international florists, as well as displays of historical documents.
properties.name: St Mary's Church, Battersea

properties.description: The home of Conway Hall Ethical Society, an organisation renowned as a hub for free speech and progressive thought. Grade II listed building with both Arts and Crafts and Art Deco features adding to its distinctive style.

images.title: Watercolour of Conway Hall by the architect
Arts and Crafts style seating in the Main Hall
Main Hall view from the stage

properties.name: Conway Hall

properties.description: Situated in one of the largest and grandest 19th century squares in London, 1 Belgrave Square was acquired by Romania in 1936 and is now home to the Romanian Cultural Institute.
properties.name: Romanian Cultural Institute

properties.description: St Anne's Limehouse has been described as 'the finest parish church in England.' Designed by Nicholas Hawksmoor, it is Grade I listed and one of the Major Churches in the Church of England. It is home to a thriving Christian congregation.
properties.name: St Anne's Church, Limehouse

properties.description: Built in the Gothic style with dressed flint and stone dressings. There are monuments to Joseph Glover (1628), Lady Dorothy Brownlow (1699), William Earl Talbot (1782) and Isaac Littlebury (1740). The churchyard has 5 Grade II tombs.

images.title: Aerial view of St Nicholas Church looking east

properties.name: St Nicholas Church

properties.name: Preedy Glass

properties.description: Grade II* Crescent House, influenced by Corbusier’s Maisons Jaoul was the final part of Golden Lane Estate and forerunner to the Barbican. Inside, our homes are as relevant today as in 1962. Outside, future proofing awaits.

images.title: View across Crescent House and the Golden Lane Estate
View across Crescent House and The Barbican
Many flats are set around open courts
Balcony flats overlook the Barbican Wildlife Garden

properties.name: Crescent House

properties.description: Our timber frame building was designed by Matrix Feminist Design Co-Operative, and built by women. It represents our community's history of activism-the same ethos that transformed our site from dereliction, into a thriving community garden

images.title: Carpenter Louise Heaps working on the building's frame
Louise Heaps (lead carpenter, left) working on the portal frames for the building

properties.name: Walworth Garden

properties.description:
A great little museum set in the Grade 2 listed Ossulston Estate - a prime example of pre-war Social housing - based on Karl Marz Hof in Vienna.
Open Tuesday to Friday 9am-5pm, plus Saturday 14th, Saturday 21st and Sunday 22nd September 11am-4pm.

images.title: A museum on the social housing Ossulston Estate - a Space for us?
Pearly Queen outside the People's Museum
Hear the story of stolen social housing art from those who restituted it. Gilbert Bayes 'Draper'

properties.name: People's Museum Somers Town

properties.description: A modern conversion of a 19th-century hop warehouse and a 1980s office building, joined by a striking helical staircase. It is the home of the Royal College of Obstetricians and Gynaecologists and other women’s health organisations.
properties.name: Royal College of Obstetricians and Gynaecologists

properties.description: Built in the 1950s, this site was originally the head offices for a large consortium of industrial spaces which produced dyes and food colourings. It is now a creative workspace with 26 studios for creative businesses and an event space.

images.title: View at night of entrance and neon signage
Ethical Colour exhibition by Colour of Saying
Ethical Colour exhibition by Colour of Saying

properties.name: Switchboard Studios

properties.description:
Andaz London Liverpool Street, a concept by Hyatt, blends rich history dating back to the 1200s with modern decor and the vibrant energy of its London neighborhood.

Step inside and join us for an open house tour led by our dedicated team!
properties.name: Andaz London Liverpool Street

properties.description: OmniDe is a two floors 100m2 office space conceived as a laboratory where Art, Design and Architecture live together. What we designed is a space that is born from the conversion of an existing accountant space into an architecture office.

images.title: OmniDe London Festival of Architecture installation in Belsize Village

properties.name: OmniDe

properties.description: Outernet London is a new entertainment district including live performance venues HERE, The Lower Third and the LED lined Urban Gallery. Join a tour of the district, led by architects Orms.
properties.name: Outernet London

properties.description: A floating acoustic architecture, playfully reframing public space as an essential community engagement through sound & site mapping. Accessed by smartphone, headphones & echoes.xyz app, the Pavilion is located outside the Serpentine Gallery,. Drawing on Oskar & Zofia Hansen’s Open Form architectural concept it is one of 15 in a series including Venice, Berlin, Dublin, Bergen and Arctic Norway.

images.title: Architectural and spatial design functions also as logo for London Pavilion audiowork
QR code to access London Open Form Pavilion of Air
Architectural design & spatial sound design for Pavilion with position in Kensington Gardens

properties.name: London Open Form Pavilion of Air

properties.description: This is a newly built and fitted out architecture studio in London Fields. We designed it as a flexible working and event space with the opportunity to align personal wellbeing and professional endeavour in one supportive space.
properties.name: AH A Studio

properties.description: On the surface Stratford is all Olympics and Westfield: this tour unearths the area's Roman and religious origins, unusual buildings, famous manufacturing pioneers, 20th century hard times and considers (from above) the impacts of its newest quarter.

images.title: Aquatic Centre & Waterworks River: Guide's own photo
Old Stratford Map, credit Newham Archives

properties.name: Stratford: past, present and future

properties.description: We propose to open the Museum of Croydon stores for an intimate guided tour of our stored collections. This activity will take approximately 1hr and can cater for a maximum of 8 people.
properties.name: Museum of Croydon Behind the Scenes Tour

properties.description: Join us for a retrofit focused open studio at Conran and Partners, award-winning architecture and interior design studio, showcasing the holistic way we integrate a retained memory into our work.
properties.name: Retaining the Memory

properties.description: A Grade II Listed building of special architectural and historic interest, it originated at the end of the 19th century, during which Walthamstow was transformed from a rural community to a bustling suburb of “London over the border".
properties.name: Walthamstow Central library

properties.description: We have been collecting objects about the history of Brent for over 50 years. Visitors can find out about an Eiffel tower in Wembley, why you might make a pilgrimage to Willesden and what the Victorian streets of Brent were really like.
properties.name: Brent Museum

properties.description: St Barnabas Church is a grade II* listed building with many Arts and Crafts designed features.
properties.name: St Barnabas Church

properties.description: A walk around Brook Green with emphasis on the buried lost river, Stamford Brook.
properties.name: Brook Green walk

properties.description: A pioneering virtual museum with a physical presence in London. We celebrate, research and record the richly diverse Jewish, refugee and wide migrant contribution to British visual culture since 1900.

images.title: The Hand Made Map of the World by Tam Joseph. Ben Uri Collection

properties.name: Ben Uri Gallery and Museum

properties.description: A guided tour of Wardian, two residential towers of 55 and 50 storeys. Wardian was inspired by the great explorer and innovator Dr Nathaniel Bagshaw Ward who was responsible for the creation of the Wardian Case, used to transport plants around the world at the height of the British Empire. The tour, led by Howells, will conclude with a complimentary drink in the rooftop sky lounge.
properties.name: Wardian: tour with Howells

properties.description: You're invited to tour the newest addition to the London Borough of Croydon's residential streetscape on Beulah Hill, Crystal Palace. Gbolade Design Studio Architects will be opening the doors and giving group tours to interested member of the public of these wonderful sustainable and health homes designed to RIBA 2030 Standards.

images.title: Image Credits: Hermitage Mews Net Zero Townhouses - Gbolade Design Studio
Image Credits: Hermitage Mews Net Zero Townhouses - Gbolade Design Studio

properties.name: Hermitage Mews Building Tours

properties.description:
St Anne's Church, SW London landmark, nicknamed Pepperpot, is celebrating 200 years (Robert Smirke 1824). The church will be open September 16, 18 and 20 for guided tours, exhibits from the archives and entries from an Art Exhibition being held in August. There will be a talk by Gill Hedley, curator and writer, and the current church 
architect, Jodie Edwards, on the evening of September 19.
properties.name: St Anne's Church Wandsworth Bicentenary

properties.description:
Will Noble, author of Croydonopolis and editor of Londonist, discusses how Croydon's reputation as a 'concrete hell' belies a truly remarkable town.  

Hear the amazing story of this much-maligned town, whose only fault was to be too far ahead of the curve. The greatest city that never was.
properties.name: Croydonopolis: The Greatest City That Never Was

properties.description: Come along on a walking tour that explores some of Central Croydon's queer history. From some lesser known aspects of Archbishop of Canterbury John Whitgift's life to Second World War Spitfire pilot Roberta Cowell and London's oldest LGBTQ+ Tennis club - we will discover the fascinating queer stories hidden in our borough.
properties.name: Queer Croydon walking tour

properties.description:
Not quite The Bishops Avenue and barely the Hampstead Garden Suburb, Winnington Road still contains an unrivalled variety of Neo-Georgian domestic buildings. Join Calum Orr on a walking tour looking to re-evaluate the street's architecture and development. 

2 of 3 walks run by the Trust.

images.title: House on Winnington Road (Hampstead Garden Suburb Trust)

properties.name: Reappraising Winnington Road

properties.description: Discover the stories of 19th century people working, living and dying across Southwark and Lambeth and the remarkable individuals who strove to make life better.  Remnants of 19th century architecture are to be found at every turn; the site of Charles Dickens' childhood trauma, a Victorian railway for the dead, a magnificent theatre still vibrant today and a street where time has stood still.

images.title: 19th century Borough High Street.  Credit: Southwark Archives

properties.name: 19th century lives in Southwark and Lambeth

properties.description: A guided tour of the burgeoning creative and life sciences hub of White City. Taking in both White City Place and Imperial's North campus, visitors will learn about the history of the area, the role of institutions like the BBC and Imperial College London in shaping its character and the reciprocal relationship that's developed between education and innovation in this fascinating part of London.
properties.name: White City Walking Tour

properties.description: From 5 to 9 pm Thursday 19 September 2024 the Hackney Wick and Fish Island Community Development Trust and Arbeit will be opening Hackney’s first-of-its-kind circular economy hub ‘The Loop’ to the public. This event will give full access to studios filled with local circular economy leaders, a free-to-attend exhibition and workshops.
properties.name: The Loop

properties.description: We are a theatre company for performers and artists with learning disabilities in the West London area.  We will screen a free immersive experience, run on a loop, entitled Red Rope. It tells a powerful story about the impact of plastic on our oceans and features artworks, dance, music and poetry by our performers and artists. We will also display works of art.

images.title: Red Rope immersive experience in our Studio Theatre

properties.name: IMPACT Community Arts Centre
